General Budget Debate, Tuesday, 02 June 2020 DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala says a big chunk of the provincial budget has had to be redirected to the Covid-19 response.
He presented the over R800-million budget for the 2020/21 financial year on Tuesday. The MEC for Human Settlements and Public Works in KwaZulu-Natal, Neliswa Peggy Nkonyeni will table the budget vote for Human  Settlements for the 2020/2021 financial year. On Wednesday, the MEC for Human Settlements and Public Works in KZN, Neliswa Peggy Nkonyeni tabled the budget vote for Human  Settlements for the 2020/2021 financial year. Nkonyeni will also table the budget vote for Public Works from 9am on Thursday, 4 June 2020.  MEC for Human Settlements and Public Works in KZN, Neliswa Peggy Nkonyeni, tables budget vote for Public Works. The MEC for Agriculture and Rural Development in KwaZulu-Natal Bongiwe Sithole-Moloi will table the 2020/21 Budget vote at 11am. MEC for Human Settlements and Public Works in KZN, Neliswa Peggy Nkonyeni, tables budget vote for Public Works. The MEC for Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs, Nomusa Dube-Ncube, will also table the 2020/2021 budget vote on Thursday at 3pm. The MEC for Social Development Nonhlanhla Khoza, will table the 2020/2021 budget on Thursday at 3pm. MEC for Human Settlements and Public Works in KZN, Neliswa Peggy Nkonyeni, tables budget vote for Public Works.